tasks.description:
Rewrite hex-cli/src/tui/chat.rs with the following changes:

### Layout
Change the 4-chunk layout constraints:
```
Constraint::Length(1),   // title bar: spinner + model
Constraint::Min(3),      // messages: borderless, flowing
Constraint::Length(1),   // thin separator rule
Constraint::Min(1),      // input: borderless, prompt-style, auto-height
Constraint::Length(1),   // status bar
```
For input height: compute `max(1, app.input.lines().count()) + 1` capped at 6, use `Constraint::Length(h)`.

### render_title
Keep as-is (1-line title bar, no border, spinner + model).

### render_messages (MAJOR REDESIGN)
Remove the Block/Borders wrapper. Build lines as:
```
for each message:
  // Role label line  
  if User: Line::from(Span::styled("  you", Style::default().fg(Color::Green).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)))
  if Assistant: Line::from(Span::styled("  hex", Style::default().fg(Color::Cyan).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)))
  // Thin rule
  Line::from(Span::styled("  " + "─".repeat(width.saturating_sub(4) as usize), Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray)))
  // Content: use crate::tui::markdown::render_markdown(&msg.content, width) for Assistant
  // For User: just plain Lines with 2-space indent
  // For streaming last assistant message: append '▌' cursor to last content line
  // Empty separator line between messages
  Line::from("")
```

For scroll: keep existing scroll logic but use borderless Paragraph (no Block):
```rust
let p = Paragraph::new(lines)
    .wrap(Wrap { trim: false })
    .scroll((scroll, 0));
f.render_widget(p, area);
```

### render_separator (NEW)
Render a full-width dim horizontal line between messages area and input:
```rust
let rule = "─".repeat(area.width as usize);
let p = Paragraph::new(rule).style(Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM));
f.render_widget(p, area);
```

### render_input (REDESIGN)
Replace the bordered input with a prompt-style borderless input:
```rust
// Build display: prepend '  ❯ ' to first line, indent subsequent lines with '    '
let display_lines: Vec<Line> = app.input.lines().enumerate().map(|(i, line)| {
    if i == 0 {
        Line::from(vec![
            Span::styled("  ❯ ", Style::default().fg(Color::Cyan)),
            Span::raw(line.to_string()),
        ])
    } else {
        Line::from(vec![
            Span::raw("    "),
            Span::raw(line.to_string()),
        ])
    }
}).collect();
// If input is empty, show placeholder
let display = if app.input.is_empty() && !app.streaming {
    vec![Line::from(vec![
        Span::styled("  ❯ ", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray)),
        Span::styled("type a message…", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)),
    ])]
} else if app.streaming {
    vec![Line::from(vec![
        Span::styled("  … ", Style::default().fg(Color::Yellow)),
        Span::styled("streaming…", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)),
    ])]
} else {
    display_lines
};
let p = Paragraph::new(display).wrap(Wrap { trim: false });
f.render_widget(p, area);
```

### render_status (MINOR UPDATE)
Make the status bar more concise and REPL-like:
```rust
let model_short = app.model.split('/').last().unwrap_or(&app.model);
let status = format!("  {} · {} tok · q/Ctrl+C quit",
    model_short,
    app.total_input_tokens + app.total_output_tokens
);
let p = Paragraph::new(status).style(Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM));
f.render_widget(p, area);
```

### Input struct change: multi-line
Change `input: String` → keep as `String` but allow embedded `\n`. Update `send_message` to use `self.input.trim()` (trims leading/trailing whitespace including newlines).

### Key handling: add Shift+Enter
In the key match arm, add:
```rust
(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::SHIFT) => {
    app.input.push('\n');
}
```
Keep `(KeyCode::Enter, KeyModifiers::NONE) => app.send_message()` unchanged.

### Layout function signature
Update `run_event_loop` to pass terminal width to render for the separator rule:
```rust
let width = terminal.size()?.width;
terminal.draw(|f| render(f, app, width))?;
```
And update `render(f: &mut Frame, app: &ChatApp, _width: u16)`.

### compile + commit
`cargo build -p hex-cli` must pass. Then:
`git add hex-cli/src/tui/chat.rs && git commit -m 'feat(hex-cli/tui): flowing REPL layout, markdown rendering, multi-line input'`
